---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---
<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Syvidea"
  description="Terms of service for the Syvidea website and sourcing service."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-page max-w-3xl prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        These Terms of Service govern your use of the Syvidea website and the sourcing and advisory
        services offered by Syvidea. By using the website or engaging with our services, you agree to
        these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What Syvidea does</h2>
      <p>
        Syvidea is a sourcing and advisory service. We help customers worldwide choose, compare,
        and source local AI workstations built on the AMD Strix Halo / AI Max+ 395 platform from our hardware
        partners (BOSGAME, PELAND, BITPC).
      </p>

      <h2>2. What Syvidea is not</h2>
      <p>
        Syvidea does not manufacture, design, or assemble the workstations. The workstations are produced by
        our hardware partners. Syvidea does not provide a hardware warranty directly; warranty terms are set
        by the partner brand.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Quotes and orders</h2>
      <p>
        All orders are quote-based. A written quote is provided for each request and must be approved before
        payment is taken. Quotes are valid for the period stated in the quote. Prices, configurations, and
        availability are subject to change until the quote is approved and payment is confirmed.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Pricing and payment</h2>
      <p>
        Prices are quoted in US dollars unless stated otherwise. Payment is taken via a payment link or
        deposit arrangement after quote approval. We do not store payment card information on this website.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Shipping and delivery</h2>
      <p>
        Shipping options, costs, and delivery windows are confirmed in the quote. Customs duties and applicable
        taxes are the buyer's responsibility unless explicitly included in the quote. See the
        <a href="/shipping">shipping page</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Warranty and returns</h2>
      <p>
        Warranty is provided by the partner brand per the partner brand's published terms. Returns and refunds
        are handled per the <a href="/refund-policy">refund policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Use of the website</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the website for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the website</li>
        <li>Interfere with or disrupt the website or the servers or networks connected to the website</li>
        <li>Use the website in any way that could damage, disable, overburden, or impair our infrastructure</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The website content, including text, graphics, logos, and design, is the property of Syvidea or its
        licensors and is protected by intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create
        derivative works without prior written consent.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The website and its content are provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. To the maximum
        extent permitted by law, Syvidea disclaims all warranties, express or implied, including warranties
        of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Syvidea shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental,
        special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred
        directly or indirectly, or any loss of data, use, or goodwill.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. The latest version will be posted on this page with
        an updated effective date.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: 2026-06-25</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</PageLayout>
